 SANParks have issued a statement cautioning guests to be careful after protests broke out at Cork Trust on the R536 heading towards Kruger Gate. The statement urged visitors to use alternative gates such as Phabeni and Numbi until the situation has calmed. ALSO READ: Two people killed in head-on collision Guests are asked to use Numbi Gate as an alternative. SANParks spokesman Isaac Phaahla told Lowvelder that people should avoid the area but that all the gates were open. He said, “The protests are taking place 40 kilometres from the park, on the R536 heading towards the Kruger Gate. Our gates are all open and operating as normal.
“We don’t know what is happening.” ALSO READ: Nkomati to close in a year’s time

Lowvelder could not reach local police to comment on the protest action.